member.summary: This command fulfills the use case of opening a project. We first check if the project needs saving, if yes, we open the save dialog. Once the file has been saved, check if open file dialog is required. Open the file dialog to select a new file.

member.name: M:Ansys.Disco.UIModule.Commands.File.OpenProjectDialogUICommand.SaveSynchronously
member.summary: Prompts the user to save the existing project before the next project is opened. The user is able to cancel the entire process, and any saving that occurs will happen synchronously.
member.returns: An .
member.remarks:
The synchronous save is necessary to ensure that it is safe to reset the environment before the following open operation. We cannot use the existing save/save-as commands because they are asynchronous: they use to ensure the correct journal-recording behavior in SpaceClaim. Consequently some of the save-as logic has been duplicated here.
REFACTOR: We should probably factor out the commonality into a separate service (although the synchronous vs asynchronous aspect might make the commonality so minimal as to be hardly worth the trouble).

member.summary: Fix for an edge case with the toggle chart button. We clear our when we close our last chart manually. So when we click the toggle button again, all of the charts will open.
member.remarks: The problem was when we only had 1 monitor open, and clicked the close button, clicking the toggle chart button will open the singular chart, whereas it should open all of them. This was because our PreviouslyOpenedCharts was never cleared and the button would open what was in there instead.

member.name: M:Ansys.Disco.UIModule.Views.SidView.GalleryToggleButton_OnClick(System.Object,System.Windows.RoutedEventArgs)
member.summary: Event handler executed when the Gallery Toggle button is clicked.
member.remarks: The Gallery Toggle button is the button that ordinarily brings up the Simulation Manager control when pressed. However, if there is only one simulation, then instead of bringing up the Simulation Manager, a Context Menu is displayed.

member.name: M:Ansys.Disco.UIModule.Views.SidView.GalleryToggleButton_OnMouseUp(System.Object,System.Windows.RoutedEventArgs)
member.summary: Event handler executed when the Gallery Toggle button is released.
member.remarks: This event is fired when the Mouse Up event occurs. However, it is not fired when the button is clicked. Instead, it is fired when the button is clicked with the right mouse button. The event needs to be handled so that the context menu is positioned properly.

member.name: M:Ansys.Disco.UIModule.Views.SidView.ShowSimulationContextMenu
member.summary: Displays and positions the simulation context menu.
member.remarks: This method is needed for two reasons. The first is that the WPF framework doesn't set some context menu properties until a context menu is activated using the right mouse button. Since the context menu needs to be displayed when the button is pressed when there is one simulation, the properties needed to be set in code rather than XAML. The second reason is that the context menu needs to be centered over the Gallery Toggle button and this is more readily accomplished in code too.
